sentences: Kim Hyung-soo (Korean: 김형수; born December 30, 1981), better known by his stage name K. Will (Korean: 케이윌), is a South Korean singer.
He debuted in 2007 and has since become known for his chart-topping ballads.
K. Will has released four full-length albums: Left Heart (2007), Missing You (2009), The Third Album (2012–2013), and The Fourth Album (2017–2018).

K. Will has released four full-length albums: Left Heart (2007), Missing You (2009), The Third Album (2012–2013), and The Fourth Album (2017–2018).
K. Will released his first album, Left Heart, on March 6, 2007 via Bang's label Big Hit Entertainment.
That year, K. Will also released the hit song, "Moon Setting Alone," from the War of Money soundtrack, and was voted the best new singer of 2007 in a survey of South Korean television writers.
In January 2008, K. Will left Big Hit and joined his agent Kim Shi-dae's new company Starship Entertainment.
On December 2, 2008, he released his first digital single under Starship, "Love 119" (a collaboration with rapper MC Mong).
K. Will released his first extended play, Dropping the Tears, featuring a title track of the same name, on March 31, 2009.
On November 5, 2009, he released his second album, Missing You.
In early December, K. Will performed at the 2009 Hallyu Music Festival in Sapporo and Toyko, Japan.
=== 2010–2011: International expansion ===
K. Will debuted in the United States at "THE THREE ROMANTICISTS" concert along with Kim Bum Soo and Yoo Seung-Chan on March 5, 2010.
His single titled "Present"  was released on March 10, 2010 and achieved #1 on many online music charts.
K. Will embarked on his first solo concert in Japan, "K. WILL Live Concert with Band in Tokyo" in May 2010 and "K. WILL Live Concert with Band in Osaka" in July 2010.
K. Will embarked on his first solo concert in Japan, "K. WILL Live Concert with Band in Tokyo" in May 2010 and "K. WILL Live Concert with Band in Osaka" in July 2010.
A year after his second album, K. Will released another digital single featuring Simon D and Hyorin of Sistar titled "Amazed" on January 21, 2011.
K. Will successfully completed his third solo concert, "My Heart Is Beating" at the Olympic Park Hall on June 25, 2011.

After joining KBS TV "Immortal Songs 2" in November 2011, K. Will left the show after winning three times, and set the new record, winning against 5 consecutive singers in the leaving episode on January 21, 2012.

sentences: 2017–present: The 4th Album ===
On July 30, 2017, K. Will stated on his personal Twitter that he would be working on completing his next album.
On May 10, 2018, K. Will released The 4th Album Part.2 #1 'Will Be a Start' as the first of a trilogy of three singles that will lead up to the release of the full The 4th Album Part.2.
On October 28, 2018, K. Will revealed the tracklist for The 4th Album Part.2 [想像; Mood Indigo], and an album teaser was released three days later.
In February 2020, K. Will renewed his contract with Starship Entertainment.
